headline: US Approves $93M Weapon Sale to India: A Boost for Defense ETFs
summary: A $93 million US weapon sale to India puts the spotlight on defense stocks like LMT and, by extension, fuels momentum for defense ETFs like SHLD.

headline: R2S receives $1.25 billion Tamir production contract for facility in Camden, Arkansas
summary: The Raytheon-Rafael Protection Systems (R2S) joint venture was awarded a $1.25 billion contract to supply Israel with Tamir surface-to-air missiles. Raytheon is an RTX (NYSE: RTX) business. The direct commercial sales contract includes missiles, missile kits and test equipment.
